<inglise> of 13 July 2000 determining the sensitive production areas and/or the groups of high-quality varieties exempt from application of the quota buyback programme in raw tobacco </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1534/2000, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks tundlikud tootmispiirkonnad ja/v&otilde;i k&otilde;rge kvaliteediga sortide r&uuml;hmad, mille suhtes ei kohaldata toortubaka kvoodi tagasiostmise programmi 13. juuli 2000 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2075/92 of 30 June 1992 on the common organisation of the market in raw tobacco(1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1336/2000(2), and in particular Article 14a thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 30. juuni 1992. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2075/92 toortubakaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1336/2000, (2) eriti selle artiklit 14a, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Under Article 34(2) of Commission Regulation (EC) No 2848/98 of 22 December 1998 laying down detailed rules for the application of Council Regulation (EEC) No 2075/92 as regards the premium scheme, production quotas and the specific aid to be granted to producer groups in the raw tobacco sector(3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1249/2000(4), the Commission must determine, on the basis of proposals from the Member States, which sensitive production areas and/or groups of high-quality varieties, up to a maximum of 25 % of each Member State's guarantee threshold, are to be exempt from application of the quota buyback programme. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) komisjoni 22. detsembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2848/98 (millega kehtestatakse &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2075/92 (toortubakasektori lisatasukavade, tootmiskvootide ja tootjar&uuml;hmadele antava eriabi kohta) kohaldamiseks, (3) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1249/2000 (4)) artikli 34 l&otilde;ike 2 kohaselt peab komisjon liikmesriikide ettepanekute p&otilde;hjal m&auml;&auml;rama kindlaks, milliste tundlike tootmispiirkondade ja/v&otilde;i k&otilde;rge kvaliteediga sortide r&uuml;hmade suhtes ei kohaldata kuni 25% ulatuses iga liikmesriigi tagatisk&uuml;nnisest kvoodi tagasiostmisprogrammi; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) At the request of certain Member States, these groups of high-quality varieties should be determined. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) teatavate liikmesriikide taotlusel tuleks need k&otilde;rge kvaliteediga sortide r&uuml;hmad kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Article 35(2) of Regulation (EC) No 2848/98 stipulates that the Member State must make public its intention to sell from 1 September so that other producers may buy the quota before it is actually bought back. Therefore this Regulation must apply from 31 August 2000. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2848/98 artikli 35 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatakse, et liikmesriigid peavad avalikustama oma m&uuml;&uuml;gisoovi enne 1. septembrit, et teised tootjad saaksid kvoodi osta enne selle tegelikku tagasiostmist; seet&otilde;ttu tuleb k&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldada alates 31. augustist 2000; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) The measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Tobacco, </inglise>
<eesti> 4) k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las tubakaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
